1
00:00:53,159 --> 00:00:54,840
That's the situation.

2
00:00:55,000 --> 00:00:56,479
Sifang just wants to run a

3
00:00:56,759 --> 00:00:58,000
high-end health preservation salon.

4
00:00:58,479 --> 00:00:59,479
I come here to diagnose and treat

5
00:00:59,640 --> 00:01:01,039
when I'm free.

6
00:01:01,159 --> 00:01:01,759
That's it.

7
00:01:02,439 --> 00:01:03,240
It's clean and clear.

8
00:01:03,799 --> 00:01:05,040
Look at you three,

9
00:01:05,400 --> 00:01:06,760
young and old,

10
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:08,159
none of you are reliable.

11
00:01:09,079 --> 00:01:10,159
Jianhua, you too.

12
00:01:10,439 --> 00:01:12,719
Can't you explain everything to your family?

13
00:01:13,480 --> 00:01:14,599
If you keep fighting like this,

14
00:01:14,719 --> 00:01:15,959
I don't mind,

15
00:01:16,159 --> 00:01:17,560
but what if it affects the customers?

16
00:01:18,719 --> 00:01:20,239
Alright, stop with the long faces.

17
00:01:20,439 --> 00:01:22,239
I'll go wash some fruit for you.

18
00:01:22,359 --> 00:01:24,439
If there's any misunderstanding, let's clear it up right now.

19
00:01:28,239 --> 00:01:28,840
Lan,

20
00:01:29,640 --> 00:01:31,319
I was being rude.

21
00:01:31,359 --> 00:01:32,319
Was that being rude?

22
00:01:32,439 --> 00:01:33,680
You were extremely rude,

23
00:01:33,799 --> 00:01:34,480
extremely rude.

24
00:01:34,599 --> 00:01:35,359
You're acting like a child.

25
00:01:36,879 --> 00:01:39,519
I just thought you did something wrong to Du Juan.

26
00:01:42,840 --> 00:01:43,879
Could it be

27
00:01:44,560 --> 00:01:45,439
that my mom

28
00:01:47,120 --> 00:01:48,680
misunderstood me for the same reason?

29
00:01:51,159 --> 00:01:51,560
Juan.

30
00:01:52,239 --> 00:01:53,000
Juan, Juan, Juan.

31
00:01:53,120 --> 00:01:53,840
Juan, Juan, Juan.

32
00:01:53,920 --> 00:01:54,400
Juan.

33
00:01:54,719 --> 00:01:55,359
I'm sorry.

34
00:01:55,400 --> 00:01:56,280
Juan, don't go.

35
00:01:56,439 --> 00:01:57,400
Can you hear me out?

36
00:01:57,519 --> 00:01:58,799
You didn't answer my calls.

37
00:01:58,879 --> 00:01:59,560
Just give me a minute.

38
00:01:59,719 --> 00:02:00,599
Or thirty seconds.

39
00:02:00,719 --> 00:02:01,280
Let me explain.

40
00:02:01,359 --> 00:02:02,560
Haven't I made myself clear?

41
00:02:02,760 --> 00:02:03,640
We're over.

42
00:02:03,879 --> 00:02:04,319
No.

43
00:02:04,480 --> 00:02:04,959
Juan.

44
00:02:05,280 --> 00:02:06,799
Don't say something so heartbreaking.

45
00:02:06,879 --> 00:02:07,319
Did you see

46
00:02:07,400 --> 00:02:08,639
the message Sifang sent me?

47
00:02:08,719 --> 00:02:09,199
Let me explain.

48
00:02:09,199 --> 00:02:10,360
I have nothing to do with Sifang.

49
00:02:11,719 --> 00:02:12,360
Duaner.

50
00:02:13,240 --> 00:02:13,759
Duaner.

51
00:02:14,319 --> 00:02:15,479
You can't abandon me.

52
00:02:15,639 --> 00:02:16,599
You are the one I love the most.

53
00:02:16,719 --> 00:02:17,360
I swear to God.

54
00:02:17,400 --> 00:02:18,520
I swear to Sun Simiao.

55
00:02:18,719 --> 00:02:20,000
You are the only one in my heart.

56
00:02:20,080 --> 00:02:21,520
Just marry me, Duaner.

57
00:02:21,719 --> 00:02:23,639
Get up, it's embarrassing.

58
00:02:23,759 --> 00:02:24,080
Duaner.

59
00:02:24,080 --> 00:02:25,159
The students are all here.

60
00:02:25,319 --> 00:02:26,599
Then, then don't be mad, okay?

61
00:02:26,960 --> 00:02:28,599
Jun'er, I have nothing with Sifang.

62
00:02:28,759 --> 00:02:29,960
She's just my former client,

63
00:02:30,159 --> 00:02:31,400
running a foot therapy shop.

64
00:02:31,520 --> 00:02:32,319
She wants to collaborate with me

65
00:02:32,400 --> 00:02:33,520
on some projects in traditional Chinese medicine.

66
00:02:33,919 --> 00:02:35,479
I just want to make some extra money.

67
00:02:36,000 --> 00:02:38,080
You're too old to make extra money.

68
00:02:39,280 --> 00:02:40,520
I'm just worried about you.

69
00:02:40,800 --> 00:02:43,000
Last time I saw you pay for that model airplane repair.

70
00:02:43,360 --> 00:02:45,120
I just want to set up a little nest egg for you.

71
00:02:45,400 --> 00:02:46,960
We can repair model airplanes next.

72
00:02:47,199 --> 00:02:47,800
Take it.

73
00:02:48,120 --> 00:02:49,039
The password is your birthday.

74
00:02:49,280 --> 00:02:50,199
I don't want it.

75
00:02:50,360 --> 00:02:51,000
I can do it myself.

76
00:02:51,159 --> 00:02:52,159
Of course I know you can do it.

77
00:02:52,280 --> 00:02:53,360
You are the best.

78
00:02:53,840 --> 00:02:54,560
But with me,

79
00:02:55,120 --> 00:02:55,879
you can do it better.

80
00:03:01,080 --> 00:03:01,639
What are you laughing at?

81
00:03:01,960 --> 00:03:02,759
I just love your teacher.

82
00:03:02,919 --> 00:03:03,360
Go.

83
00:03:03,479 --> 00:03:04,039
Go.

84
00:03:05,439 --> 00:03:06,400
I just love your teacher.

85
00:03:07,520 --> 00:03:08,240
This kid.

86
00:03:09,039 --> 00:03:10,439
Cuckoo, don't be mad.

87
00:03:11,360 --> 00:03:12,759
I really miss you in this part.

88
00:03:14,039 --> 00:03:15,439
You know, some people say

89
00:03:15,560 --> 00:03:16,439
that when you feel bad,

90
00:03:16,599 --> 00:03:18,000
you love to read poetry.

91
00:03:18,199 --> 00:03:19,960
I found a poem written by an author the other day.

92
00:03:20,159 --> 00:03:21,319
It's really good.

93
00:03:21,960 --> 00:03:22,400
Take a look.

94
00:03:22,840 --> 00:03:24,039
I've copied it for you.

95
00:03:25,639 --> 00:03:26,919
Your handwriting has improved recently.

96
00:03:31,400 --> 00:03:32,800
Every sentence is written to the heart.

97
00:03:34,159 --> 00:03:35,240
Look who wrote it.

98
00:03:48,199 --> 00:03:49,240
Glad to meet you.

99
00:04:04,520 --> 00:04:05,400
So cheesy.

100
00:04:06,199 --> 00:04:06,759
So cheesy.

101
00:04:07,159 --> 00:04:07,719
So cheesy.

102
00:04:08,479 --> 00:04:09,479
I've seen his book.

103
00:04:09,960 --> 00:04:11,080
His poems are cheesy.

104
00:04:11,479 --> 00:04:12,639
His pen name is cheesy, too.

105
00:04:12,800 --> 00:04:14,639
It's called "The Letter Paper Cuckoo".

106
00:04:15,039 --> 00:04:16,360
Why doesn't he call himself "The Free-range Chicken"?

107
00:04:16,680 --> 00:04:17,399
Really.

108
00:04:18,240 --> 00:04:19,120
Dad, you don't know.

109
00:04:20,720 --> 00:04:21,480
Know what?

110
00:04:21,759 --> 00:04:22,879
The pen name

111
00:04:23,399 --> 00:04:24,439
belongs to mom.

112
00:04:27,240 --> 00:04:28,560
Your mom's pen name is Juan Shangjuan?

113
00:04:28,920 --> 00:04:29,720
She also writes poetry?

114
00:04:30,680 --> 00:04:32,000
She's been writing since she was young.

115
00:04:32,120 --> 00:04:32,720
She's been writing all along.

116
00:04:33,480 --> 00:04:34,079
You don't know?

117
00:04:42,519 --> 00:04:43,720
Juan Shangjuan.

118
00:04:51,319 --> 00:04:51,959
What's wrong?

119
00:04:53,240 --> 00:04:53,839
Nothing.

120
00:04:55,639 --> 00:04:57,240
Is this this morning's newspaper?

121
00:04:57,800 --> 00:04:58,680
Why do you take so long to read the paper?

122
00:04:58,800 --> 00:05:00,199
To know everything about Changchun.

123
00:05:00,360 --> 00:05:02,079
Who's as unworldly as you?

124
00:05:02,279 --> 00:05:03,160
Comrade Yunfeng,

125
00:05:03,279 --> 00:05:04,839
reading the paper helps you grasp the pulse of the times.

126
00:05:04,959 --> 00:05:06,000
I suggest you learn from me.

127
00:05:06,160 --> 00:05:06,759
Okay.

128
00:05:14,160 --> 00:05:14,639
Hello?

129
00:05:16,120 --> 00:05:16,480
Okay.

130
00:05:17,800 --> 00:05:18,959
You've contacted the supplier?

131
00:05:20,160 --> 00:05:21,079
Give me his number.

132
00:05:21,439 --> 00:05:22,160
I'll keep an eye on it myself.

133
00:05:29,759 --> 00:05:30,240
Okay.

134
00:05:35,920 --> 00:05:36,519
Okay.

135
00:05:37,920 --> 00:05:38,600
I'll be there soon.

136
00:06:12,040 --> 00:06:12,600
Brother,

137
00:06:13,240 --> 00:06:14,639
I'll treat you to this meal.

138
00:06:15,279 --> 00:06:15,879
This soup

139
00:06:16,319 --> 00:06:16,879
is made by me.

140
00:06:18,040 --> 00:06:18,600
I'll get you

141
00:06:19,600 --> 00:06:20,199
a bowl.

142
00:06:23,759 --> 00:06:25,120
Look at your shaking hands.

143
00:06:25,279 --> 00:06:25,959
Doctor Lan,

144
00:06:26,600 --> 00:06:28,519
can you rely on

145
00:06:28,879 --> 00:06:29,920
rely on your acupuncture?

146
00:06:33,480 --> 00:06:34,160
Let me do it.

147
00:06:56,839 --> 00:06:57,439
Jun.

148
00:06:58,959 --> 00:06:59,600
How about

149
00:07:00,560 --> 00:07:01,279
we have a drink?

150
00:07:01,560 --> 00:07:02,079
Sure.

151
00:07:02,319 --> 00:07:03,079
Okay, I'll get it.

152
00:07:05,040 --> 00:07:05,920
Sit down, sit down.

153
00:07:07,160 --> 00:07:09,399
I'm treating you to dinner today.

154
00:07:09,720 --> 00:07:10,600
You don't need to fuss around.

155
00:07:10,920 --> 00:07:11,480
What's up?

156
00:07:11,680 --> 00:07:13,720
Eager to be the head of the family?

157
00:07:18,800 --> 00:07:20,240
I'm not in a hurry to be the head of the family.

158
00:07:20,839 --> 00:07:21,519
Brother.

159
00:07:22,240 --> 00:07:23,639
It's just that everyone here

160
00:07:27,120 --> 00:07:28,040
is also my family.

161
00:07:30,399 --> 00:07:31,360
Your family?

162
00:07:32,519 --> 00:07:34,279
This used to be my home.

163
00:07:34,800 --> 00:07:35,759
These young men

164
00:07:35,959 --> 00:07:37,160
are my sons.

165
00:07:37,720 --> 00:07:38,439
Uncle Yun.

166
00:07:40,079 --> 00:07:42,560
That's not very nice to say.

167
00:07:42,720 --> 00:07:43,199
Xiaochuan.

168
00:07:44,720 --> 00:07:45,279
Don't interrupt.

169
00:07:48,160 --> 00:07:48,920
Enough.

170
00:07:49,519 --> 00:07:50,279
Stop it.

171
00:07:51,160 --> 00:07:52,399
This is my home.

172
00:07:52,879 --> 00:07:54,199
If you don't want to eat,

173
00:07:54,399 --> 00:07:55,160
get out.

174
00:08:02,319 --> 00:08:03,160
Today,

175
00:08:04,560 --> 00:08:05,519
I have something to say.

176
00:08:10,480 --> 00:08:11,639
I'm with Jianhua

177
00:08:13,040 --> 00:08:14,240
on my own decision.

178
00:08:15,439 --> 00:08:16,759
I don't care about anyone's face,

179
00:08:17,360 --> 00:08:18,279
or if anyone is happy.

180
00:08:19,759 --> 00:08:20,639
From now on,

181
00:08:21,920 --> 00:08:23,319
Lan Jianhua is my husband.

182
00:08:27,240 --> 00:08:28,199
Please respect him.

183
00:08:29,519 --> 00:08:30,519
In a few days,

184
00:08:31,959 --> 00:08:33,399
we're going to take wedding photos.

185
00:08:34,360 --> 00:08:35,360
I'm telling you in advance.

186
00:08:36,960 --> 00:08:37,840
I'm leaving Changchun

187
00:08:40,000 --> 00:08:40,960
tomorrow

188
00:08:42,000 --> 00:08:43,600
to go south for a while.

189
00:08:44,240 --> 00:08:45,200
Are you leaving?

190
00:08:47,559 --> 00:08:48,799
I want to learn from the young people.

191
00:08:48,919 --> 00:08:49,639
I'm going on a road trip

192
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:52,240
to see the beautiful landscapes of our country.

193
00:09:09,000 --> 00:09:09,759
The soup is good,

194
00:09:11,120 --> 00:09:13,559
but it's a bit undercooked.

195
00:09:14,879 --> 00:09:16,000
Next time,

196
00:09:16,840 --> 00:09:19,000
cook it a bit longer.

197
00:09:20,559 --> 00:09:22,279
This stove at home

198
00:09:22,600 --> 00:09:23,679
isn't as strong

199
00:09:24,120 --> 00:09:25,039
as it used to be.

200
00:09:30,600 --> 00:09:31,159
Alright,

201
00:09:32,039 --> 00:09:33,639
I've said my piece.

202
00:09:33,960 --> 00:09:34,840
Everyone, enjoy your meal.

203
00:09:35,919 --> 00:09:36,679
Once you're done,

204
00:09:38,120 --> 00:09:39,440
I should go pack up.

205
00:10:20,080 --> 00:10:21,159
You're here to dance.

206
00:10:22,879 --> 00:10:24,360
I just came to see.

207
00:10:24,440 --> 00:10:25,440
You're late.

208
00:10:25,960 --> 00:10:27,320
The people have all left.

209
00:10:27,720 --> 00:10:28,360
Next time,

210
00:10:28,720 --> 00:10:29,360
come earlier.
